# Chunked Execution and Handoff

- Break work into small chunks that can be completed in one session.
- Use `docs/TODO2.md` as the single source of truth for chunk status.
- At the start of work, read `docs/TODO2.md` and pick one `CHUNK-XX`.
- Do not run large multi-phase implementations in one pass unless explicitly requested.
- After each chunk, update `docs/TODO2.md`:
  - mark status
  - list files changed
  - write the next best step
  - note blockers/risks
- Prefer resumable outputs over long explanations to reduce token usage.
- When the user says they will switch threads, leave a clear handoff entry in `docs/TODO2.md`.
- If chunk scope is unclear, propose 2-4 concrete chunk options and ask which to do now.
